1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel deep learning method for local self-supervised representation learning, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed method on downstream classification tasks in the visual domain, indicating a focus on computer vision. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method involves training deep neural networks without labels or end-to-end backpropagation, which is a significant advancement in the field of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of biological neural networks as inspiration for the proposed method, indicating a connection to the field of neural computing. 
5. cs.SD (Sound): The paper also demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed method on downstream classification tasks in the audio domain, indicating a potential connection to the field of sound.
